      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DASHING DARLEY (1) finds it hard to win. Better run when finding the frame last time though, finishing second (17.17) at this track. Solid record at the distance winning four races. One of the contenders. JAZZY BOO (8) failed to feature last start after drifting back at Mt Gambier, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at Mt Gambier (17.61) beating Speechless in a Grade 6 on May 3. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. Has ability and can atone. RUSSO (2) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at his last four runs. Last time finished 2nd on May 8 over 400m at Gawler behind Sebon Disco beaten 3 lengths (23.30) in a Other. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and six minor placings to his credit. Well-placed to take this out. ANTECEDENT (5) will have admirers again after placing as favourite last time out.",
